voices.name: Abaddon

voices.mp3Text: Alchemy? No, my friends, merely humble swordplay.
voices.name: Alchemist

voices.mp3Text: Not ancient enough, it appears, to know better.
voices.name: Ancient Apparition

voices.mp3Text: You require a bit more fire in your belly to take me on.
voices.name: Ancient Apparition

voices.mp3Text: You didn't blink far enough, Anti-Mage.
voices.name: Anti-Mage

voices.mp3Text: Hm! I can still find humor in killing those who lack it.
voices.name: Anti-Mage

voices.mp3Text: You didn't need to die, Arc Warden. I was going to end this war either way.
voices.name: Arc Warden

voices.mp3Text: You're too weak to stop the Ancients. Leave this one to me.
voices.name: Arc Warden

voices.mp3Text: Even with the obvious embellishment, your stories have gone stale, Axe.
voices.name: Axe

voices.mp3Text: , you are a sorry disappointment…
voices.name: Axe

voices.mp3Text: A nightmare is merely an opportunity for heroism!
voices.name: Bane

voices.mp3Text: Ew. What's this purple goo on my sword?
voices.name: Bane

voices.mp3Text: Your noble creature died for your misdeeds, Batrider.
voices.name: Batrider

voices.mp3Text: See, Batrider? I always find a way to gain the upper hand.
voices.name: Batrider

voices.mp3Text: I lay your soul to rest with honor, Karroch.
voices.name: Beastmaster

voices.mp3Text: We could have been allies. Then you might still be alive.
voices.name: Beastmaster

voices.mp3Text: What do you know! The blood was inside of you this whole time.
voices.name: Bloodseeker

voices.mp3Text: best find a new lapping dog.
voices.name: Bloodseeker

voices.mp3Text: paid you enough to die.
voices.name: Bounty Hunter

voices.mp3Text: I'll tell you a secret: I wanted you to find me.
voices.name: Bounty Hunter

voices.mp3Text: This was the famous Brewmaster? It appears he must have been sober…
voices.name: Brewmaster

voices.mp3Text: Our orders are friendly with one another. It didn't need to come to this.
voices.name: Brewmaster

voices.mp3Text: You can't run away from me again, swine!
voices.name: Bristleback

voices.mp3Text: Mothers and children first!
voices.name: Broodmother

voices.mp3Text: Your crude efforts amount to nothing.
voices.name: Centaur Warrunner

voices.mp3Text: I came through your lands once. Surely they must still sing of my exploits.
voices.name: Centaur Warrunner

voices.mp3Text: A bit of chaos is good. But you're too much.
voices.name: Chaos Knight

voices.mp3Text: Would you rather be buried in your homeland or with these pompous fools?
voices.name: Chen

voices.mp3Text: To compel another into service is to deny the very breath of life.
voices.name: Chen

voices.mp3Text: Believe me. This was mercy.
voices.name: Clinkz

voices.mp3Text: To be honest, I thought he was dead already…
voices.name: Clinkz

voices.mp3Text: Imitation is the highest form of flattery, but this armor is all natural.
voices.name: Clockwerk

voices.mp3Text: No armor exists that can stop this blade.
voices.name: Clockwerk

voices.mp3Text: had high hopes for you… oh well.
voices.name: Crystal Maiden

voices.mp3Text: Don't look at me. It was a miracle she survived this long.
voices.name: Crystal Maiden

voices.mp3Text: You overthought things, my friend. My path to victory was quite simple.
voices.name: Dark Seer

voices.mp3Text: Did it ever occur to you that you may have merely been the smartest among a race of imbeciles?
voices.name: Dark Seer

voices.mp3Text: Oh ho ho, Dazzle. That tickled.
voices.name: Dazzle

voices.mp3Text: Even a shallow grave is deep enough.
voices.name: Dazzle

voices.mp3Text: Consider your wish granted.
voices.name: Death Prophet

voices.mp3Text: To face death with a laugh is admirable. To beg for it… pathetic.
voices.name: Death Prophet

voices.mp3Text: Why that was hardly a disruption at all.
voices.name: Disruptor

voices.mp3Text: , aren't we?
voices.name: Disruptor

voices.mp3Text: Argue all you like, but at the heart of it, you're nothing more than a spoiled aristocrat.
voices.name: Doom

voices.mp3Text: I feel like I should hum a funeral march…
voices.name: Doom

voices.mp3Text: I thought you might be more remarkable than a normal dragon. Apparently not.
voices.name: Dragon Knight

voices.mp3Text: chose his final vessel poorly.
voices.name: Dragon Knight

voices.mp3Text: You shouldn't have let me get that close, Traxex.
voices.name: Drow Ranger

voices.mp3Text: Playtime in the woods is over.
voices.name: Drow Ranger

voices.mp3Text: Every stone crumbles if you strike the right place.
voices.name: Earth Spirit

voices.mp3Text: You should have known this would happen when you rolled up on me.
voices.name: Earth Spirit

voices.mp3Text: I merely made the battlefield barrier free.
voices.name: Earthshaker

voices.mp3Text: Do you feel the earth shaking? I don't feel it shaking…anymore.
voices.name: Earthshaker

voices.mp3Text: You might be the oldest thing I've ever killed.
voices.name: Elder Titan

voices.mp3Text: I don't fix broken things, Titan. I merely dispose of them.
voices.name: Elder Titan

voices.mp3Text: Huh. I thought you were going to run away. As usual.
voices.name: Ember Spirit

voices.mp3Text: These scales are fire proof. Well, close enough.
voices.name: Ember Spirit

voices.mp3Text: Would that I could have spared you, my dear.
voices.name: Enchantress

voices.mp3Text: You did not deserve to die by my blade. But, what's done is done.
voices.name: Enchantress

voices.mp3Text: I don't care where you came from. This is where you end.
voices.name: Enigma

voices.mp3Text: I will put my faith in the fundamentals of style.
voices.name: Enigma

voices.mp3Text: I had to wipe that hideous smile off your face.
voices.name: Faceless Void

voices.mp3Text: It's a pity you never got to see my splendor.
voices.name: Faceless Void

voices.mp3Text: Remember, Mireska. This was not my choice, but yours.
voices.name: Dark Willow

voices.mp3Text: You didn't have to choose this path Mireska.
voices.name: Dark Willow

voices.mp3Text: I told you it wasn't safe to trust such fragile machinery.
voices.name: Gyrocopter

voices.mp3Text: are all the same… All toys, no substance.
voices.name: Gyrocopter

voices.mp3Text: You think you can break me?!
voices.name: Huskar

voices.mp3Text: Well, at least you fought like your life depended upon it.
voices.name: Huskar

voices.mp3Text: Any corpse knows the same number of spells, Invoker. Zero.
voices.name: Invoker

voices.mp3Text: Of all the smug faces I've bloodied, yours was the worst.
voices.name: Invoker

voices.mp3Text: Too predictable, little friend.
voices.name: Io

voices.mp3Text: Poor thing. Didn't survive the surgery.
voices.name: Jakiro

voices.mp3Text: My blade does not merely dance, Yurnero. It sings!
voices.name: Juggernaut

voices.mp3Text: After the stories I'd heard of your prowess, I was hoping you'd last longer than that… Pity.
voices.name: Juggernaut

voices.mp3Text: This is where negligence leads, old man.
voices.name: Keeper of the Light

voices.mp3Text: So do I keep the light now? Is that how it works?
voices.name: Keeper of the Light

voices.mp3Text: I expected better footwork from a sailor.
voices.name: Kunkka

voices.mp3Text: What to do with a drunken sailor? Simple. Stab him in the heart.
voices.name: Kunkka

voices.mp3Text: I could not help but notice you only challenge the weak, Tresdin.
voices.name: Legion Commander

voices.mp3Text: That is how a real duel ends.
voices.name: Legion Commander

voices.mp3Text: That was for her…
voices.name: Leshrac

voices.mp3Text: Have you forgotten my oath, Leshrac? This time is the next time.
voices.name: Leshrac

voices.mp3Text: Does it hurt less the second time?
voices.name: Lich

voices.mp3Text: I usually feel some sympathy for fallen foes. But for you? Nothing…
voices.name: Lich

voices.mp3Text: Why is it always my responsibility to dispatch the grotesques?
voices.name: Lifestealer

voices.mp3Text: I did not steal your life. But I certainly did take it.
voices.name: Lifestealer

voices.mp3Text: I hope you made peace with your sister… it's not good to die with guilt.
voices.name: Lina

voices.mp3Text: It's not personal, Lina. You're simply in my way.
voices.name: Lina

voices.mp3Text: Time for another vacation, witch.
voices.name: Lion

voices.mp3Text: I told you, Lion. If we met again there would be consequences.
voices.name: Lion

voices.mp3Text: You should've left the bear at home.
voices.name: Lone Druid

voices.mp3Text: Hopefully no one was depending on you…
voices.name: Lone Druid

voices.mp3Text: has poor taste in protectors.
voices.name: Luna

voices.mp3Text: . It did not need to come to this.
voices.name: Luna

voices.mp3Text: Down, boy!
voices.name: Lycan

voices.mp3Text: In some cities, they pay decent coin for this kind of work.
voices.name: Lycan

voices.mp3Text: Fear not, Magnus. I'll make sure no one finds your horn.
voices.name: Magnus

voices.mp3Text: Gods, you're stubborn. No wonder you're dead.
voices.name: Magnus

voices.mp3Text: How does the saying go? Cut the head off made of sna-- No, that's not it…
voices.name: Medusa

voices.mp3Text: That was nothing. You should have seen the time I rolled into a pit of basilisks.
voices.name: Medusa

voices.mp3Text: had in store for you…
voices.name: Meepo

voices.mp3Text: A shovel. Really?
voices.name: Meepo

voices.mp3Text: , Mirana.
voices.name: Mirana

voices.mp3Text: 's royal protector.
voices.name: Mirana

voices.mp3Text: Leave the mischief to the children, Wu Kong.
voices.name: Monkey King

voices.mp3Text: You came all this way, Wu Kong. The least I could do was kill you.
voices.name: Monkey King

voices.mp3Text: It appears my movements were more fluid, Morphling.
voices.name: Morphling

voices.mp3Text: Your water dance is overrated.
voices.name: Morphling

voices.mp3Text: weren't so uptight, you might have died amongst them.
voices.name: Naga Siren

voices.mp3Text: Now I see why your people cast you out.
voices.name: Naga Siren

voices.mp3Text: And so you find your head on the chopping block, Prophet.
voices.name: Nature's Prophet

voices.mp3Text: And that is for dulling my blade on your bark!
voices.name: Nature's Prophet

voices.mp3Text: For those fallen in your wake, I strike you down!
voices.name: Necrophos

voices.mp3Text: Some days I love my job more than others. This is one of those days.
voices.name: Night Stalker

voices.mp3Text: Day or night. It makes no difference to me!
voices.name: Night Stalker

voices.mp3Text: You're a feckless coward, Nyx. The world is better without you.
voices.name: Nyx Assassin

voices.mp3Text: I did not need to see you, Nyx. I could smell you coming from miles away.
voices.name: Nyx Assassin

voices.mp3Text: You were a magnificent creature Magi… I am sorry to dispatch you.
voices.name: Ogre Magi

voices.mp3Text: I thought of killing only one of you, but I did not want the other one to get lonely.
voices.name: Ogre Magi

voices.mp3Text: Life is too short to waste time arguing with you, Purist.
voices.name: Omniknight

voices.mp3Text: Just die already!
voices.name: Omniknight

voices.mp3Text: And that's why we fight the battle, Oracle.
voices.name: Oracle

voices.mp3Text: So you can see the future and you still picked the losing side?
voices.name: Oracle

voices.mp3Text: I don't do well with authority figures.
voices.name: Outworld Devourer

voices.mp3Text: You should have stayed on the sidelines.
voices.name: Outworld Devourer

voices.mp3Text: I admire your style, sister. Well… admired.
voices.name: Phantom Assassin

voices.mp3Text: Fitting punishment for the dour.
voices.name: Phantom Assassin

voices.mp3Text: Were you in such a hurry to die, Lancer?
voices.name: Phantom Lancer

voices.mp3Text: Look on the bright side… when you come back, you'll get the pleasure of losing to me again.
voices.name: Phoenix

voices.mp3Text: Do you think my blade is not swift enough to bring you down?
voices.name: Phoenix

voices.mp3Text: Regardless of true age, one should take no pleasure in killing the young.
voices.name: Puck

voices.mp3Text: Cute tricks, Puck. Well, they would have been if you had survived.
voices.name: Puck

voices.mp3Text: Ugh. And I thought he smelled bad on the outside.
voices.name: Pudge

voices.mp3Text: I have little patience for child's play.
voices.name: Pugna

voices.mp3Text: It's time someone gave you proper discipline.
voices.name: Pugna

voices.mp3Text: It seems our game went too far, my dear.
voices.name: Queen of Pain

voices.mp3Text: A quick and painless death for you, Akasha.
voices.name: Queen of Pain

voices.mp3Text: I don't even know why, but killing you felt…rewarding.
voices.name: Razor

voices.mp3Text: Where do you freaks keep coming from anyway?
voices.name: Razor

voices.mp3Text: No, you see, it's funny because you were here to assassinate me.
voices.name: Riki

voices.mp3Text: You may copy me, Rubick, but you'll never have my sense of style.
voices.name: Rubick

voices.mp3Text: You're out of your element, Sand King.
voices.name: Sand King

voices.mp3Text: for a better set of armor.
voices.name: Sand King

voices.mp3Text: Ugh, did you make that body yourself?
voices.name: Shadow Demon

voices.mp3Text: What can I say? You looked a little full.
voices.name: Shadow Fiend

voices.mp3Text: All the souls in existence could not fill that void, Shadow Fiend.
voices.name: Shadow Fiend

voices.mp3Text: That was a neat trick. Was it supposed to end in your death?
voices.name: Shadow Shaman

voices.mp3Text: You cannot take the high road with me, deceiver.
voices.name: Shadow Shaman

voices.mp3Text: There's nothing left to say, Silencer.
voices.name: Silencer

voices.mp3Text: As you can see, I do a bit of silencing myself.
voices.name: Silencer

voices.mp3Text: Now you'll never redeem yourself, Skywrath.
voices.name: Skywrath Mage

voices.mp3Text: Of all the mistakes you've made, facing me was probably the worst.
voices.name: Skywrath Mage

voices.mp3Text: Next time we'll do it under water, just to be fair.
voices.name: Slardar

voices.mp3Text: Your blade is sly, Slark, but not nearly swift enough to catch me.
voices.name: Slark

voices.mp3Text: You can't steal what I've got, Slark. You've got to earn it.
voices.name: Slark

voices.mp3Text: It wasn't a sharp eye you needed, Kardel.
voices.name: Sniper

voices.mp3Text: Such toys are no match for a fine blade.
voices.name: Sniper

voices.mp3Text: I needed to address this before things got out of hand.
voices.name: Spectre

voices.mp3Text: I don't even know how to insult you properly…
voices.name: Spectre

voices.mp3Text: All I did was hold out my blade.
voices.name: Spirit Breaker

voices.mp3Text: That's what you get for barging in.
voices.name: Spirit Breaker

voices.mp3Text: Is that how you separate the man from spirit? Or is it always a package deal?
voices.name: Storm Spirit

voices.mp3Text: Did you think you could escape?!
voices.name: Storm Spirit

voices.mp3Text: I'm not foolish enough to stand in front of that blade, Sven. It's all about positioning.
voices.name: Sven

voices.mp3Text: That is a fight they will be telling stories about. Well, my part anyway.
voices.name: Sven

voices.mp3Text: Listen. We told you not to come. This is what you get.
voices.name: Techies

voices.mp3Text: You don't acquire skills like these in a library, Lanaya.
voices.name: Templar Assassin

voices.mp3Text: Let me tell you a deadtime story…
voices.name: Templar Assassin

voices.mp3Text: I've killed, you're certainly the tallest.
voices.name: Terrorblade

voices.mp3Text: Bored now.
voices.name: Terrorblade

voices.mp3Text: will need to find a new favorite.
voices.name: Tidehunter

voices.mp3Text: Where did all that anxiety get you, Rizzrack?
voices.name: Timbersaw

voices.mp3Text: Now maybe you will get the help you need.
voices.name: Timbersaw

voices.mp3Text: A rapier does not need to recharge.
voices.name: Tinker

voices.mp3Text: You best not have marred my blade!
voices.name: Tiny

voices.mp3Text: You were never going to be fast enough for me.
voices.name: Tiny

voices.mp3Text: Rest easy, Treant. I shall protect the forest in your stead.
voices.name: Treant Protector

voices.mp3Text: And that is how you plant a tree.
voices.name: Treant Protector

voices.mp3Text: just feels right.
voices.name: Troll Warlord

voices.mp3Text: Brute force was never enough to best me, Troll.
voices.name: Troll Warlord

voices.mp3Text: Confidence only goes so far.
voices.name: Tusk

voices.mp3Text: That is how I roll, Tusk.
voices.name: Tusk

voices.mp3Text: I do not have time for your one track mind, Underlord.
voices.name: Underlord

voices.mp3Text: Next!
voices.name: Underlord

voices.mp3Text: I guess it was finally your time.
voices.name: Undying

voices.mp3Text: They said you could not die. I've been told lies before.
voices.name: Undying

voices.mp3Text: I expected more from you, Ursa.
voices.name: Ursa

voices.mp3Text: Did you think I would let you off easy for old time's sake?
voices.name: Ursa

voices.mp3Text: Here is a little something to remember me by…
voices.name: Vengeful Spirit

voices.mp3Text: Ah, thank you. My plates needed a good cleaning.
voices.name: Venomancer

voices.mp3Text: He was more annoying than anything.
voices.name: Venomancer

voices.mp3Text: Perhaps I must find your homeland. Just one of you wasn't even a challenge.
voices.name: Viper

voices.mp3Text: Your poison is sweet like a summer wine.
voices.name: Viper

voices.mp3Text: I may be on your list, Visage. But not today.
voices.name: Visage

voices.mp3Text: Don't you have a day job?
voices.name: Visage

voices.mp3Text: What good is a book against a fine blade?
voices.name: Warlock

voices.mp3Text: Life on the battlefield offers no tenure, Warlock.
voices.name: Warlock

voices.mp3Text: Hunting bugs never gets old.
voices.name: Weaver

voices.mp3Text: I could not let you off with only a tongue lashing.
voices.name: Weaver

voices.mp3Text: A cold wind blows for you tonight, Lyralei.
voices.name: Windranger

voices.mp3Text: You should have kept running.
voices.name: Windranger

voices.mp3Text: This is what happens when you spend too much time reading about life instead of living it.
voices.name: Winter Wyvern

voices.mp3Text: So does your collection of mystical artifacts now belong to me?
voices.name: Winter Wyvern

voices.mp3Text: In my professional opinion? You're dead.
voices.name: Witch Doctor

voices.mp3Text: So how do I shrink your head for a keepsake?
voices.name: Witch Doctor

voices.mp3Text: All that suffering, I revisit upon you ten fold!
voices.name: Wraith King

voices.mp3Text: How many times must I kill you?
voices.name: Wraith King

voices.mp3Text: Is that what they call a god where you come from?
voices.name: Zeus

voices.mp3Text: From all the stories I'd heard, I expected something more…
voices.name: Zeus

voices.mp3Text: First blood!
The swiftest blade will take the day!
The first blood runs from my blade.
First blood! It is as expected, yes.
First blood! With so much more to come.

text: Before the 20 minute mark, within 1000 radius

voices.mp3Text: If I pierce you, Abaddon, does the font flow dry?
voices.name: Abaddon

voices.mp3Text: Two on one? My favorite odds.
voices.name: Alchemist

voices.mp3Text: This time I'll not settle for a draw!
voices.name: Bristleback

voices.mp3Text: Arachnia... I've no interest in consuming your young, merely in crushing them.
voices.name: Broodmother

voices.mp3Text: Which one, which one? No matter, I'll simply pierce them all.

voices.mp3Text: Io, Io, Io.... What are we going to do with you?

voices.mp3Text: How do you even fly with that massive growth on your--- Ooh, I see

voices.mp3Text: The old adage holds true: If it bleeds, we can kill it.

voices.mp3Text: I could kill you with my eyes closed, Riki. Like so!
voices.name: Riki

voices.mp3Text: Watch and learn, Rubick.
voices.name: Rubick

voices.mp3Text: I cannot refuse a challenge, but between us, killing demons got old long ago.
voices.name: Shadow Demon

voices.mp3Text: You can't even breathe properly. How are you supposed to fight?
voices.name: Slardar

voices.mp3Text: Don't kill yourself before I get the chance, Techies.
voices.name: Techies

voices.mp3Text: The only thing filling your belly will be my blade, Tidehunter.
voices.name: Tidehunter

voices.mp3Text: Hahaha. Have you seen yourself, Tinker?
voices.name: Tinker

voices.mp3Text: Cheer up, Venge. You're going to die either way.
voices.name: Vengeful Spirit

voices.mp3Text: business, it gets tiring, no?
voices.name: Abaddon

voices.mp3Text: I like this mist, Abaddon. It lends an air of mystery!
voices.name: Abaddon

voices.mp3Text: You look like a newborn, Razzil. Riding around like that.
voices.name: Alchemist

voices.mp3Text: So can you make any good potions? Hm? You know the kind I mean...
voices.name: Alchemist

voices.mp3Text: Are you brighter than you were yesterday?
voices.name: Ancient Apparition

voices.mp3Text: Does anything surprise you anymore, Kaldr?
voices.name: Ancient Apparition

voices.mp3Text: Don't you think you're taking things a bit far?
voices.name: Anti-Mage

voices.mp3Text: I think it's great you and Silencer are spending quality time together.
voices.name: Anti-Mage

voices.mp3Text: So this whole mess is all your fault?
voices.name: Arc Warden

voices.mp3Text: Didn't I just see you over there?
voices.name: Arc Warden

voices.mp3Text: Axe, you're arrogant, hot tempered, and entirely too bold. I like it.
voices.name: Axe

voices.mp3Text: , Axe. Not too much, anyway.
voices.name: Axe

voices.mp3Text: May I walk in front? I don't want to step in... whatever that is.
voices.name: Bane

voices.mp3Text: I had a terrible dream where you stole all the kills, Bane.
voices.name: Bane

voices.mp3Text: Do not take this as an insult, but why does the bat put up with you?

voices.mp3Text: The bat, what does she eat?
voices.name: Batrider

voices.mp3Text: Tell me what's on the horizon, my friend!
voices.name: Beastmaster

voices.mp3Text: Remember the last time we teamed up?
voices.name: Beastmaster

voices.mp3Text: I will be upfront about this: I'm not much for ritualistic slaughter.
voices.name: Bloodseeker

voices.mp3Text: You may lick the drippings from my blade, if you wish.
voices.name: Bloodseeker

voices.mp3Text: Point out the valuable ones, Gondar. We'll kill them first.
voices.name: Bounty Hunter

voices.mp3Text: Mireska could have a future... don't take it from her.
voices.name: Bounty Hunter

voices.mp3Text: You must be well drunk to think you can split into three.
voices.name: Brewmaster

voices.mp3Text: Think not of our past differences, Bristleback. Today, we fight as brothers.
voices.name: Bristleback

voices.mp3Text: Turning your back to a foe just seems foolish to me.
voices.name: Bristleback

voices.mp3Text: So you're fighting to protect your babies...by making your babies fight?
voices.name: Broodmother

voices.mp3Text: Can I walk in this web of yours without getting stuck?
voices.name: Broodmother

voices.mp3Text: Smile, Centaur. The fighting's about to begin.
voices.name: Centaur Warrunner

voices.mp3Text: fight... hopfully you can match their ferocity.
voices.name: Centaur Warrunner

voices.mp3Text: Ha I'm sorry. It is just hard to take serious one who takes themselves so seriously.
voices.name: Chaos Knight

voices.mp3Text: , I trust you'll make the correct choice.
voices.name: Chaos Knight

voices.mp3Text: So your thing is animal husbandry? I hear there's good money in that.
voices.name: Chen

voices.mp3Text: As long as you don't deal in sentient animals, we're good here.
voices.name: Chen

voices.mp3Text: This is a good look for you, Clinkz.
voices.name: Clinkz

voices.mp3Text: You see: that is why I rarely do the bidding of kings. Give me a rabble of commonfolk anyday.
voices.name: Clinkz

voices.mp3Text: You fashioned this suit of armor yourself? Marvelous!
voices.name: Clockwerk

voices.mp3Text: never cease to amaze me.
voices.name: Clockwerk

voices.mp3Text: You need to get out more, my dear.
voices.name: Crystal Maiden

voices.mp3Text: Listen. I talked to Lina, and I think she might be willing to make amends.
voices.name: Crystal Maiden

voices.mp3Text: I kind of like to play it by ear, if you get my point.
voices.name: Dark Seer

voices.mp3Text: Just don't tell me what to do and we will be fine.
voices.name: Dark Seer

voices.mp3Text: Wait until the last moment, Dazzle. It will be more dramatic this way.
voices.name: Dazzle

voices.mp3Text: Do not despair, my dear prophet. I'm sure you'll die as soon as we win this.
voices.name: Death Prophet

voices.mp3Text: Try to look on the bright side of life.
voices.name: Death Prophet

voices.mp3Text: Tell me you're not still upset, Disruptor. I truly meant no disrespect.
voices.name: Disruptor

voices.mp3Text: So this umbral pact. It's a hard rule, or more like a guideline?
voices.name: Doom

voices.mp3Text: Now I must ask myself what other stories I thought false are actually true...
voices.name: Doom

voices.mp3Text: was up to?
voices.name: Dragon Knight

voices.mp3Text: The coloring of your plates is truly marvelous, Davion.
voices.name: Dragon Knight

voices.mp3Text: , Davion? Or does it seem too much like killing one's own kind?
voices.name: Dragon Knight

voices.mp3Text: There is beauty in the flight of your arrows, ranger.
voices.name: Drow Ranger

voices.mp3Text: Life is not meant to be lived alone, Traxex. Today, we fight together. Tomorrow we celebrate!
voices.name: Drow Ranger

voices.mp3Text: Impressive, Kaolin. But can you match my distance?

voices.mp3Text: We could make a game of this, Kaolin!
voices.name: Earth Spirit

voices.mp3Text: I swear, shaker. If you say "Let's roll" one more time...
voices.name: Earthshaker

voices.mp3Text: We all see the beauty in a good Blink Dagger, friend, but even I think you might have a problem.
voices.name: Earthshaker

voices.mp3Text: I would never call them lies, but some of these origin stories are a bit far-fetched, no?
voices.name: Elder Titan

voices.mp3Text: Cheer up, friend. If the world weren't broken, there would be no opportunity for greatness.
voices.name: Elder Titan

voices.mp3Text: So how many of you brothers are there, anyway? I've heard conflicting reports.
voices.name: Ember Spirit

voices.mp3Text: I must say, Ember, you certainly know how to make an entrance.
voices.name: Ember Spirit

voices.mp3Text: Enchantress... Again we find our causes to be in alignment.
voices.name: Enchantress

voices.mp3Text: Were adventure not my mistress, we might have had a chance.
voices.name: Enchantress

voices.mp3Text: I heard you have a special method for dealing with poachers. Tell me more...
voices.name: Enchantress

voices.mp3Text: So you're telling me it's not really a hole at all? I'm speechless.
voices.name: Enigma

voices.mp3Text: I'm trying to figure you out, mon ami...
voices.name: Enigma

voices.mp3Text: If only you could see that smile in a mirror, my friend. I mean, then you could see how awkward it is.
voices.name: Faceless Void

voices.mp3Text: You do me no favors by meddling with time. Life is meant to be lived... not perfected.
voices.name: Faceless Void

voices.mp3Text: You had every advantage, Mireska. Yet you come to this...

voices.mp3Text: There's good in you, Mireska. You don't have to be a miscreant. You can be a hero!
voices.name: Dark Willow

voices.mp3Text: You say you want to forge your own path, but all you're doing is following in your father's footsteps!
voices.name: Dark Willow

voices.mp3Text: It is nice to see someone so active in his later years.
voices.name: Gyrocopter

voices.mp3Text: So what did you do before retirement?
voices.name: Gyrocopter

voices.mp3Text: You will not draw blood before me, Huskar.
voices.name: Huskar

voices.mp3Text: A little showmanship might go a long way, Huskar.
voices.name: Huskar

voices.mp3Text: Your art is a thing of beauty, Invoker. Your personality, however...
voices.name: Invoker

voices.mp3Text: Invoker, I stopped listening as soon as I heard you talk.
voices.name: Invoker

voices.mp3Text: Time for a good old fashioned ambush. Right, Io?
voices.name: Io

voices.mp3Text: Wherever I go, I feel your presence around me. Is that strange?
voices.name: Io

voices.mp3Text: You're not graceful, mon ami. But you get the job done.
voices.name: Jakiro

voices.mp3Text: Do you each do a wing? How does it work?
voices.name: Jakiro

voices.mp3Text: The brooding loner thing is a bit cliché?, n'est-ce pas?
voices.name: Juggernaut

voices.mp3Text: I know a thing or two about dangerous paramours... trust me my friend, the sooner you apologize to Lanaya, the safer you will be.
voices.name: Juggernaut

voices.mp3Text: You make me laugh, old man. Perhaps you're not as senile as you appear to be.
voices.name: Keeper of the Light

voices.mp3Text: Chaos Knight was asking about you. It seems he is quite taken with you.
voices.name: Keeper of the Light

voices.mp3Text: Finally a man with a sense of style!
voices.name: Kunkka

voices.mp3Text: I may share certain rogue-like qualities, but I assure you Admiral -- I am no pirate.
voices.name: Kunkka

voices.mp3Text: ? A lesser man would have been jealous.
voices.name: Legion Commander

voices.mp3Text: , Tresdin... you will get no sympathy from me.
voices.name: Legion Commander

voices.mp3Text: I let you live before, Leshrac. But forgiveness will not come easily.
voices.name: Leshrac

voices.mp3Text: I don't know what's come over me, fighting beside the likes of you...
voices.name: Leshrac

voices.mp3Text: Tell me, do the undead sleep?
voices.name: Lich

voices.mp3Text: You have one job to do, Lich. Do not make me regret this.
voices.name: Lich

voices.mp3Text: Poor creature. I do not envy what you have become.
voices.name: Lifestealer

voices.mp3Text: Blink twice if you prefer that I put you out of your misery...
voices.name: Lifestealer

voices.mp3Text: is a lonely place to live... perhaps when the battle is over you'd like some company? Hm?

voices.mp3Text: Trust me. A bit of contrition goes a long way...
voices.name: Lina

voices.mp3Text: is your favorite, Lion? I prefer the second. Or perhaps the seventh.
voices.name: Lion

voices.mp3Text: 's gifts have strings attached.
voices.name: Lion

voices.mp3Text: I cannot claim such divine charge as yours, druid. My purpose is always my own...and not carefully kept!
voices.name: Lone Druid

voices.mp3Text: How does the bear know what you want him to do?
voices.name: Lone Druid

voices.mp3Text: Do you not miss the secular life, Luna?
voices.name: Luna

voices.mp3Text: ? Does that not get confusing?
voices.name: Luna

voices.mp3Text: How old are you in dog years, Lycan?
voices.name: Lycan

voices.mp3Text: Which form feels more natural to you at this point, Lycan?
voices.name: Lycan

voices.mp3Text: You always know just the right thing to say, Magnus. A remarkable gift.
voices.name: Magnus

voices.mp3Text: Much like your horn, many covet the natural gifts of my kind.
voices.name: Magnus

voices.mp3Text: When this is over, Medusa, I will help you on your quest. I can do no less.

voices.mp3Text: I should have liked to have seen you in your heyday, Medusa.
voices.name: Medusa

voices.mp3Text: a considerable debt, no?
voices.name: Meepo

voices.mp3Text: ... Gondar does not play fair.
voices.name: Meepo

voices.mp3Text: I, too, know the burdens of noble birth, Mirana. And the allure to break away.
voices.name: Mirana

voices.mp3Text: . Pity to have missed it.
voices.name: Mirana

voices.mp3Text: Tell me your name again? Monkey Man?
voices.name: Monkey King

voices.mp3Text: You talk too much, Wu Kong. But nothing to say to me, eh?
voices.name: Monkey King

voices.mp3Text: Sentient water? This gets better every day!
voices.name: Morphling

voices.mp3Text: The covers are impressive, Morphling, but do you have any original shapes?
voices.name: Morphling

voices.mp3Text: I sincerely hope you'll grace us all with a song. At the appropriate time, of course.

voices.mp3Text: Those are some lovely scales you have. Nothing compared to mine, of course. But nice!
voices.name: Naga Siren

voices.mp3Text: So do the trees like what you do to them, Prophet?

voices.mp3Text: I prefer a straight up fight to all this sneaking around, but sometimes victory does require a bit of subterfuge.
voices.name: Nature's Prophet

voices.mp3Text: You give off a bad air, friend.

voices.mp3Text: Your time will come, Necrophos. I'll see to it.

voices.mp3Text: Cruelty for the sake of it... I do not approve.
voices.name: Night Stalker

voices.mp3Text: I did not want to say anything in front of the others, but your breath could use a bit of peppermint... Or something.
voices.name: Night Stalker

voices.mp3Text: Tell me, Nyx... Is your hive nearby?
voices.name: Nyx Assassin

voices.mp3Text: I have never seen one like you before, Nyx. But you smell wonderful.
voices.name: Nyx Assassin

voices.mp3Text: The bonds of brotherhood are irreplaceable. Cherish them.

voices.mp3Text: You have got some drool on your chins, Ogre.
voices.name: Ogre Magi

voices.mp3Text: Are there rules against smiling in your order, Omniknight?

voices.mp3Text: Yes, I know what you have told me. But there is little proof in words.
voices.name: Omniknight

voices.mp3Text: Don't tell me how it turns out, Oracle. It's more fun to be surprised.
voices.name: Oracle

voices.mp3Text: Tell me one thing, Oracle. On the day of my funeral... Will she weep for me?
voices.name: Oracle

voices.mp3Text: So what do they do for fun where you come from?
voices.name: Outworld Devourer

voices.mp3Text: It's my first time working with whatever it is you are. Anything I should know about?
voices.name: Outworld Devourer

voices.mp3Text: Perhaps a contract is not so different from a formal challenge...
voices.name: Phantom Assassin

voices.mp3Text: ... the merchant kings will not be too happy with your sisters.
voices.name: Phantom Assassin

voices.mp3Text: 's reputation precedes you.
voices.name: Phantom Assassin

voices.mp3Text: I can see why you do not return home... What is the quiet life compared to this?
voices.name: Phantom Lancer

voices.mp3Text: before I had my chance, Azwraith. But in light of your current situation, I cannot say the grudge has held.
voices.name: Phantom Lancer

voices.mp3Text: Ah, such plumage. A rare creature indeed.
voices.name: Phoenix

voices.mp3Text: Phoenix... you play a dangerous game.
voices.name: Phoenix

voices.mp3Text: You like to ride it right to the edge, do you not, Phoenix?
voices.name: Phoenix

voices.mp3Text: You were making mischief before my plates even hardened.
voices.name: Puck

voices.mp3Text: What is the opposite of old soul? That's what you are, Puck.
voices.name: Puck

voices.mp3Text: You have really let yourself go, Pudge.
voices.name: Pudge

voices.mp3Text: . Those were dark times indeed.
voices.name: Pudge

voices.mp3Text: It is quite difficult to annoy me, Pugna... But you do an excellent job.
voices.name: Pugna

voices.mp3Text: Stop playing with your Nether Blast and push!
voices.name: Pugna

voices.mp3Text: A little pain to let us know we're alive. Right, Akasha?
voices.name: Queen of Pain

voices.mp3Text: Do not take this the wrong way, but your armor falls, uh, somewhere short of practical...
voices.name: Queen of Pain

voices.mp3Text: I'm sorry, Razor. But I cannot relate.
voices.name: Razor

voices.mp3Text: Riki, how long have you been here?
voices.name: Riki

voices.mp3Text: I thought I smelled the spices of your lands, Riki.
voices.name: Riki

voices.mp3Text: You are certainly grand, Magus, but can you do this?
voices.name: Rubick

voices.mp3Text: 's shadow, Rubick. The world awaits.
voices.name: Rubick

voices.mp3Text: I will not soon forget the cuisine in your lovely homeland.
voices.name: Sand King

voices.mp3Text: You take yourself entirely too seriously, Shadow Demon.
voices.name: Shadow Demon

voices.mp3Text: I've seen patchwork armor before, but patchwork arms? That is a new one.
voices.name: Shadow Demon

voices.mp3Text: What is the punishment, if I may ask, for breaking this umbral pact? Do such things apply to me?
voices.name: Shadow Fiend

voices.mp3Text: I love magic tricks, Rhasta. Show me another!
voices.name: Shadow Shaman

voices.mp3Text: How does one decide between a chicken, a frog, and a sheep?
voices.name: Shadow Shaman

voices.mp3Text: Why so serious, Silencer?
voices.name: Silencer

voices.mp3Text: We cannot regret the paths untaken, Skywrath.
voices.name: Skywrath Mage

voices.mp3Text: , you should have told her, my friend.
voices.name: Skywrath Mage

voices.mp3Text: I have no issue with your strategy, Slardar. But your technique exposes you.
voices.name: Slardar

voices.mp3Text: Should I let you catch your breath, Slardar?
voices.name: Slardar

voices.mp3Text: I, too, have been named criminal, Slark. Many times. Unjust laws were made to be broken.
voices.name: Slark

voices.mp3Text: I was once a wanted man, Slark. But of course I never saw the inside of a cell. They would have had to catch me!
voices.name: Slark

voices.mp3Text: I won't go so far as to call it cowardly, Sniper, but your weapon lacks a certain dignity.
voices.name: Sniper

voices.mp3Text: Best stay hidden, little friend. There's no place for you on the front lines.
voices.name: Sniper

voices.mp3Text: We will keep them busy elsewhere, Spectre. But call if you're in need.
voices.name: Spectre

voices.mp3Text: I literally do not know what you want from me, Spectre.
voices.name: Spectre

voices.mp3Text: Nothing quite like a battle charge to get the blood flowing.
voices.name: Spirit Breaker

voices.mp3Text: You know, Raijin, you're the only one of the lot with even the whiff of personality.
voices.name: Storm Spirit

voices.mp3Text: You seem a bit jumpy today, Raijin. Too much strongblack?
voices.name: Storm Spirit

voices.mp3Text: Such a blade seems impractically large, mon ami.
voices.name: Sven

voices.mp3Text: Ahh, such joie de vivre these Techies have!
voices.name: Techies

voices.mp3Text: I'm sure you're very nice, Techies. You would be even nicer if you went away.
voices.name: Techies

voices.mp3Text: Forget the secrets of the universe, Lanaya. I can share with you the secrets of happiness.
voices.name: Templar Assassin

voices.mp3Text: I know the games you play Lanaya...but I do not think Yurnero is capable of jealousy.
voices.name: Templar Assassin

voices.mp3Text: Your name is a terrible misnomer, but at least you enjoy what you do.
voices.name: Terrorblade

voices.mp3Text: Do not take this the wrong way, but I hope you're one of a kind...
voices.name: Terrorblade

voices.mp3Text: When the battle's done, we feast, Tidehunter!
voices.name: Tidehunter

voices.mp3Text: So what do you do with the tide once you catch it?
voices.name: Tidehunter

voices.mp3Text: Come now, Timbersaw. Loosen up a little and enjoy yourself.
voices.name: Timbersaw

voices.mp3Text: Once this battle is done, we get you the help you need.
voices.name: Timbersaw

voices.mp3Text: The line between this machine of yours and sorcery is, uh, a bit too subtle for me.
voices.name: Tinker

voices.mp3Text: By what means do you power this marvel of yours, Tinker?
voices.name: Tinker

voices.mp3Text: All this talk of rolling... Tiny, you don't roll!
voices.name: Tiny

voices.mp3Text: You're starting to grow on me, rockman.
voices.name: Tiny

voices.mp3Text: Sorry. I will try not to destroy too many trees.
voices.name: Treant Protector

voices.mp3Text: You certainly do take your time, Treant...
voices.name: Treant Protector

voices.mp3Text: A little personality might go a long way, Troll.
voices.name: Troll Warlord

voices.mp3Text: Is Warlord an earned title, or self-appointed?
voices.name: Troll Warlord

voices.mp3Text: Would you like to race, Tusk?
voices.name: Tusk

voices.mp3Text: Ohh, do I have something good in store for us. Just you wait.
voices.name: Tusk

voices.mp3Text: Are we there yet, Underlord? I kid, I kid.
voices.name: Underlord

voices.mp3Text: You are not going to leave me hanging when the time comes, are you?
voices.name: Underlord

voices.mp3Text: I just have a difficult time understanding the motivations of the undead. That's all.
voices.name: Undying

voices.mp3Text: Undying... Can you do something about the flies?
voices.name: Undying

voices.mp3Text: I never was much for sleep either. So much else to do!
voices.name: Ursa

voices.mp3Text: Together again, eh Ursa?
voices.name: Ursa

voices.mp3Text: If only we'd met sooner, my dear, there would be no vengeance to take.
voices.name: Vengeful Spirit

voices.mp3Text: Normally I don't put much stock in the vengeance game. But today, I will make an exception.
voices.name: Vengeful Spirit

voices.mp3Text: Do you like spicy food, Venomancer?
voices.name: Venomancer

voices.mp3Text: There might be something wrong with your liver, Venomancer...
voices.name: Venomancer

voices.mp3Text: do a possess a certain grace, despite all reports.
voices.name: Viper

voices.mp3Text: Am I correct in assuming I should avoid the noxious green puddles left in your wake?
voices.name: Viper

voices.mp3Text: So who are you chasing these days, Visage?
voices.name: Visage
